/**
 * @file graph_ssml_mc20.dox
 * @brief Detailed documentation for specialized graph classes within the AnalysisG framework for SSML MC20 events.
 *
 * @page SSML_MC20Graphs_page SSML_MC20 Graphs
 *
 * @section SSML_MC20Graphs_intro Introduction
 * The `graph_ssml_mc20.pyx` module defines a collection of specialized graph classes tailored for Semi-Supervised Machine Learning (SSML) Monte Carlo 20 (MC20) events within the AnalysisG framework. These classes, including `GraphJets`, `GraphJetsNoNu`, `GraphDetectorLep`, and `GraphDetector`, all inherit from the generic `GraphTemplate`. They encapsulate specific C++ graph types, providing a high-performance and Python-friendly interface to detailed graph structures relevant to SSML MC20 analyses.
 *
 * @section SSML_MC20Graphs_classes Specialized Graph Classes
 * Each class below is a `cdef class`, indicating its implementation as a Cython extension type. They all inherit from `GraphTemplate`, gaining its base functionalities for graph indexing, tree association, and pre-selection management. Their primary role is to wrap a specific C++ graph object, allowing for specialized data access and manipulation.
 *
 * @subsection SSML_MC20Graphs_GraphJets_class GraphJets Class
 * - **Introduction**: Represents a graph constructed from reconstructed jets in SSML MC20 events.
 * - `__cinit__(self)`: Initializes a new C++ `graph_jets` object and assigns its pointer to `self.ptr`.
 * - `__init__(self)`: Python initializer, intentionally empty.
 * - `__dealloc__(self)`: Deallocates the C++ `graph_jets` object via `self.ptr`.
 *
 * @subsection SSML_MC20Graphs_GraphJetsNoNu_class GraphJetsNoNu Class
 * - **Introduction**: Represents a graph constructed from reconstructed jets, excluding neutrinos, in SSML MC20 events.
 * - `__cinit__(self)`: Initializes a new C++ `graph_jets_nonu` object and assigns its pointer to `self.ptr`.
 * - `__init__(self)`: Python initializer, intentionally empty.
 * - `__dealloc__(self)`: Deallocates the C++ `graph_jets_nonu` object via `self.ptr`.
 *
 * @subsection SSML_MC20Graphs_GraphDetectorLep_class GraphDetectorLep Class
 * - **Introduction**: Represents a graph focusing on detector-level leptons in SSML MC20 events.
 * - `__cinit__(self)`: Initializes a new C++ `graph_jets_detector_lep` object and assigns its pointer to `self.ptr`.
 * - `__init__(self)`: Python initializer, intentionally empty.
 * - `__dealloc__(self)`: Deallocates the C++ `graph_jets_detector_lep` object via `self.ptr`.
 *
 * @subsection SSML_MC20Graphs_GraphDetector_class GraphDetector Class
 * - **Introduction**: Represents a graph constructed from general detector-level objects in SSML MC20 events.
 * - `__cinit__(self)`: Initializes a new C++ `graph_detector` object and assigns its pointer to `self.ptr`.
 * - `__init__(self)`: Python initializer, intentionally empty.
 * - `__dealloc__(self)`: Deallocates the C++ `graph_detector` object via `self.ptr`.
 *
 * @section SSML_MC20Graphs_cpp_interaction C++ Interaction
 * All classes in this module leverage Cython's capabilities for seamless C++ integration:
 * - `cdef class ...`: Declares each class as a Cython extension type.
 * - `cdef <cpp_type> *ptr`: A C++ pointer to a specific graph type (e.g., `graph_jets*`, `graph_detector*`), managed by the Cython class.
 * - `from AnalysisG.core.graph_template cimport GraphTemplate`: Imports the base `GraphTemplate` class, from which all these specialized classes inherit.
 * - `from AnalysisG.graphs.ssml_mc20.graph_ssml_mc20 cimport *`: Imports the C++ graph class declarations from their `.pxd` file.
 */
